        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 4:03PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 403 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Downtown Concord, or near Charlotte Motor
Speedway, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Downtown Concord, Kannapolis, Northeast Charlotte, West Concord,
Harrisburg, Mt Pleasant, University City, Charlotte Motor Speedway,
Hidden Valley, and Reedy Creek Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
